ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: Methods, procedures, and tests performed to diagnose disease, disordered function, or disability.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure or test to diagnose a disease or disorder.

Property.preferredDefinition: (beh-NINE) Not cancerous; does not invade nearby tissue or spread to other parts of the body.:Clinical manifestations that can be either objective when observed by a physician, or subjective when perceived by the patient.

Concepts.definition: For neoplasms, a non-infiltrating and non-metastasizing neoplastic process that is characterized by the absence of morphologic features associated with malignancy (e.g., severe atypia, nuclear pleomorphism, tumor cell necrosis, and abnormal mitoses). For other conditions, a process that is mild in nature and not dangerous to health.
Clinical, laboratory or molecular evidence, or absence of evidence of disease.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A congenital (due to inherited enzyme abnormality) or acquired (due to failure of a metabolic important organ) disorder resulting from an abnormal metabolic process.

Concepts.definition: A congenital (due to inherited enzyme abnormality) or acquired (due to failure of a metabolic important organ) disorder resulting from an abnormal metabolic process.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A group of inherited disorders characterized by structural alterations within the hemoglobin molecule.

Concepts.definition: An inherited disorder characterized by structural alterations of a globin chain within the hemoglobin molecule.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A rare and often fatal inherited disease in which the bone marrow fails to produce red blood cells, white blood cells, platelets, or a combination of these cells. The disease may transform into myelodysplastic syndrome or leukemia.

Concepts.definition: An autosomal recessive genetic disorder characterized by bone marrow failure, skeletal abnormalities, and an increased incidence of the development of neoplasias.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Any abnormality, anatomical or biochemical, evident at birth or during the neonatal period.: A disorder in which the immune system is unable to mount an adequate immune response.

Concepts.definition: Any abnormality, anatomical or biochemical, evident at birth or during the neonatal period.
A disorder in which the immune system is unable to mount an adequate immune response.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The inability of the bone marrow to produce hematopoietic elements.

Concepts.definition: The inability of the bone marrow to produce hematopoietic elements.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A rare but potentially life-threatening disorder characterized by the proliferation of histiocytes and macrophages and phagocytosis of red blood cells, white blood cells, and platelets. It may be inherited or secondary, due to infections, autoimmune disorders, or underlying malignancies. Signs and symptoms include fever, lymphadenopathy, hepatomegaly, splenomegaly, and pancytopenia.

Concepts.definition: A rare, but potentially life-threatening disorder, characterized by the proliferation of histiocytes and macrophages, and phagocytosis of red blood cells, white blood cells, and platelets. It may be inherited or secondary due to infections, autoimmune disorders, or underlying malignancies. Signs and symptoms include fever, lymphadenopathy, hepatomegaly, splenomegaly, and pancytopenia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Refers to cells that develop into connective tissue, blood vessels, and lymphatic tissue.: A benign and excessive tumor-like growth of mature cells and normal tissues which grow in a disorganized pattern.

Concepts.definition: Refers to cells that develop into connective tissue, blood vessels, and lymphatic tissue.
A benign and excessive tumor-like growth of mature cells and normal tissues which grow in a disorganized pattern.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Relating to or containing blood vessels.: A benign vascular lesion characterized by the formation of capillary-sized or cavernous vascular channels.

Concepts.definition: Relating to or containing blood vessels.
A benign vascular lesion characterized by the formation of capillary-sized or cavernous vascular channels.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Refers to the liver.: A neoplasm arising from the epithelium.  It may be encapsulated or non-encapsulated but non-invasive.  The neoplastic epithelial cells may or may not display cellular atypia or dysplasia.  In the gastrointestinal tract, when dysplasia becomes severe it is sometimes called carcinoma in situ.  Representative examples are pituitary gland adenoma, follicular adenoma of the thyroid gland, and adenomas (or adenomatous polyps) of the gastrointestinal tract.

Concepts.definition: Pertaining to, affecting, or associated with the liver.

A neoplasm arising from the epithelium.  It may be encapsulated or non-encapsulated but non-invasive.  The neoplastic epithelial cells may or may not display cellular atypia or dysplasia.  In the gastrointestinal tract, when dysplasia becomes severe it is sometimes called carcinoma in situ.  Representative examples are pituitary gland adenoma, follicular adenoma of the thyroid gland, and adenomas (or adenomatous polyps) of the gastrointestinal tract.
